<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-156-490  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 156 490.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Transactions on Computers  Jan 1990 v39 n1 p111(13).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>HYTREM - a hybrid text-retrieval machine for large databases.andO;(technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lee, Dik Lun; Lochovsky, Frederick H.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A text-retrieval machine, HYTREM (hybrid text-retrieval machine),is developed that uses a signature file approach to access largeunformatted text databases with reasonable speed and with alow-overhead access structure that reduces the amount of text tobe scanned.andP;  Text retrieval of such databases requires extensiveprocessing time because of the amount of data to be searched andthe complexity of the retrieval process.andP;  HYTREM consists of asignature processor subsystem based on a word-parallel, bit-serial(WPBS) organization for signature file searching; a text processorsubsystem, ALTEP (associative linear text processor), consistingof a linear array of logic cells for pattern matching; ahigh-speed multiple-response resolver for transferring databetween the two highly parallel WPBS and ALTEP processors; and acost-effective mass-storage subsystem.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     System DesignText Data BasesData Base ProcessorsResearch and DevelopmentNew TechniqueMass MemoryInformation Storage and RetrievalPattern MatchingMemory ManagementAssociative Memory.andO;Feature:   illustrationcharttable.andO;Caption:   Block diagram for a TRS based on signature files. (chart)A WPBS signature processor and its serial comparator. (chart)Instruction set and format. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>